    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"816344\">@Aaron Liu</span> is there a way to go from <code>deriv</code> to <code>HasDerivAt</code>? </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hf'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">deriv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t'</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">τ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">τ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">unfold</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">norm_num</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>this can be done automatically by <code>norm_num</code>, but when I tried using <code>HasDerivAt</code> everything has to been done manually like you did here. Is this simply a matter of <code>antitone</code> not having the API to take the <code>deriv</code> form directly or is there a deeper reason? Feels like this is much more complicated than it needs to be</p>",
        "id": 514170080,
        "sender_full_name": "ZhiKai Pong",
        "timestamp": 1745511894
    },
